### Steps to Reproduce

1. Define a class which will be used as a static resource:

```
    public class StaticResourceClass
    {
        //Nullable Enum - ok.
        public FontAttributes? FontAttributes
        {
            get; set;
        }

        //Nullable primitive types - ok.
        public double? FontSize
        {
            get; set;
        }

        //Nullable complex struct - problem.
        public Color? TextColor
        {
            get; set;
        }

        //Nullable complex struct - problem.
        public Thickness Padding
        {
            get; set;
        }
    }
```

2. Include the `StaticResourceClass` into a page as a StaticResource.

```
    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <ns1:StaticResourceClass x:Key="_key" TextColor="Black"">
        </ns1:StaticResourceClass>
    </ContentPage.Resources>
```

3. Run the project.

### Expected Behavior
The app should run without a problem.

### Actual Behavior
An unhandled runtime exception is thrown:
System.InvalidProgramException: Invalid IL code in XamarinForms.MainPage:InitializeComponent (): IL_0172: newobj    0x0a000023

